args:
Julietta secrets herself into a small border
church, where she listens in on a conversation
between perditionists. She is soon discovered,
but makes an escape thanks to Tobias and other
allies. Afterward, the party realizes turbulence
is roiling within the Ilian Church once more.
(There's far too much security in place\nhere for a small, out-of-the-way church.\nThat must mean my information is good.)
...And there's no doubt that the Other was\nin possession of the Auspex's body?
Yes, which means there can be only one\nconclusion: The Other was reborn and then\nsubsequently destroyed.
Unfortunate. Had we been able to make\ndirect contact with the Other, we might\nhave been able to prove our righteousness.
(This is definitely a perditionist meeting.\nI can listen in from this aisle here...)
But the actions of the seventh scion defy\ncomprehension; he seems to have fled\nthe capital and proceeded north.
There must be quite the situation at hand.\nEither way, this is a prime opportunity for\nus to continue propagating our message.

Indeed. It is precisely at this moment,
with the kingdom in disarray, that our
teachings of truth are most necessary.
We must guide Her people in all things.
Yet how do you propose we deal with the\nradicals? They are clearly up to some\nmischief, though I know not what.
To make use of the Other's name is\nunforgivable. How ought we deal with it?
It would be best not to get involved for\nnow. And besides, if they serve to weaken\nthe royal family, that stands to benefit us.
(Radicals? Using the Other's name?\nWhat in the world are they talking about?)
(Blast, I cannot hear them anymore.\nI must get closer and...)
You there! What are you doing?!
I am loath to turn my weapon against a\nfollower of the Goddess, but needs dictate\nmy course...
Urgh! I...I cannot stand against you!
All crowing and no claws, eh?
Who is this woman, and why did she\nspeak the name of the Grand Paladyn?
I've not laid eyes upon this one before.\nBut rest assured, I shall question her\nand ascertain who and what she is.
Do so. And if the situation calls for it,\nyou have my leave to dispatch her.
Understood. I will keep her confined\nuntil she wakes.
You need to get yourself together.

I can't believe you came here and marched
right into a perditionist meeting. Do you
know what would have happened had I
not followed you?

And further, you spoke Elisanne's name!
You are a spy, and yet might as well have
writ your true identity large across the wall
for all the world to see!
I know. I was careless. I couldn't help\nbut think of her in that moment and...
I, too, am curious about the Church's\ninternal activities out here.
But do not think that an excuse to continue\nyour reckless actionsâ€”especially when it\ncomes to setting out on your own.
I will bear that in mind. But for now,\nI should get myself far from this place.
I would very much like that, but I fear\nmatters are rather more complicated.
Well, well! Here we are, searching for our\ninvading little insect, and what do we find\nbut Tobias the traitor!
This is a fine opportunity; we will sanction\nand silence you in one fell swoop by\nleaving your bones here to rot!
Words unworthy of even being called droll.\nThose frightened by their own weakness\never seek to put up a bold front.
I'll enjoy feeding those words back to you.\nPaladyns or no, what do you two hope to\naccomplish, outnumbered as you are?

It is always best to have an accurate
assessment of your enemy's numbers.
Erring there leaves your judgment resting
on faulty premise.
Your comrades are in the process of taking\na bit of a nap over there, I fear.
Hope! Cibella! What are you doing here?!
Tobias set it all up. He's got a keen eye\nfor seeing and understanding these kinds\nof situations.
We infiltrated with Tobias,\nthen waited nearby.
You see? Acting entirely alone\nis the height of recklessness.
Now then, it would appear you are two \nshort, and we are two moreâ€”but we are\nwilling to fight, if you still desire it.
Damn you! I'll remember this!\nYou will PAY for what you've done!
How can I ever show my gratitude?
Aw, it was no big deal.
Any would do the same to aid a friend.
I hope you appreciate all they have\ndone for you, Julietta.
...That aside, I have to say, the Church\ncertainly has been in a worrisome state\nas of late.

Indeed, it seems a number of competing
interests have their blades drawn upon
one another behind the scenes.
We can't be too careful.
I hope nothing ill comes of all this...
